  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A group is a [monoid](../../prealgebra/terms/monoid.md) $(G, cdot, e)$ in which every element $g$ has an inverse $g^{-1}$ satisfying $g cdot g^{-1} = e = g^{-1} cdot g$. Equivalently, a group is a set equipped with an associative binary operation, an [identity element](../../prealgebra/terms/identity-element.md), and inverses for every element.",
